        <p>Converts the cursor to Loop mode, which lets you create a "loop" shape by clicking in the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">image</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">frame</MadCap:conditionalText> and dragging a rectangle area. When you release the cursor, a loop shape is created. This is a useful shape for circling content that you want to emphasize. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Loop_Properties_Dialog.htm" target="" title="" alt="" MadCap:conditions="Products.Capture">Loop Properties Dialog</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../Interface/UI_Elements/Object_Properties_Window_Pane.htm#LoopObjectProperties" MadCap:conditions="Products.Mimic">Loop Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
